A Johannesburg school has been hit by tragedy. The teachers from Riverlea High School have been killed in a car crash. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Another tragedy has struck the Johannesburg school community. Three teachers from Riverlea High died in a car accident on Sunday. The Gauteng Education Department received the news on Wednesday and sent a team to the school. Department of Educations spokesperson, Steve Mabona says MEC Panyaza Lesufi is on his way to the school. More details to follow.